unit VSoft.AnsiConsole.Emoji;

{
  Emoji shortcodes and named constants - mechanical port from Spectre's
  Emoji.Generated.cs (~1428 entries).

  Source: I:\Github\spectre.console\src\Spectre.Console\Generated\
          Spectre.Console.SourceGenerator\
          Spectre.Console.SourceGenerator.Emojis.EmojiGenerator\
          Emoji.Generated.g.cs
  Imported: 2026-04-26

  Codepoints above U+FFFF are emitted as UTF-16 surrogate pairs (Delphi's
  `string` is UTF-16; a single Char is 16 bits). E.g. U+1F9EE (Abacus) is
  encoded as `#$D83E#$DDEE`.

  Usage:
    s := TEmoji.Get('smile');                  // returns the unicode glyph
    s := TEmoji.Replace('Hello :smile:');      // substitutes shortcodes inline
    s := EmojiNames.Smile;                     // direct named-constant access
    TEmoji.Remap('smile', EmojiNames.Heart);   // override a shortcode

  The markup parser auto-calls TEmoji.Replace on text segments so existing
  markup strings with :name: tokens work unchanged.
}

